    "Example of parameters include the the temperature value, specific stop tokens, and the number of completions.",
    "Temperature.",
    "The temperature controls randomness in decoding: a temperature of 0 corresponds to deterministic decoding, while a temperature of 1 corresponds to probabilistic sampling from the model's distribution.",
    "We use temperature-scaling for scenarios requiring diverse outputs but set the temperature to zero for tasks demanding deterministic behavior (i.e.",
    "classification tasks)."
